South African Stocks Slide to Four-Month Low as Commodities Drop on Japan

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-03-15T08:18:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/south-african-stocks-slide-to-four-month-low-as-commodities-drop-on-japan.html
South African stocks fellto a more-
than four-month low, led by Anglo American Plc and BHP Billiton
Plc, as commodities declined for a fourth day after  Japan ’s
biggest earthquake spurred concern demand will shrink.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index slumped as much as 2.4
percent to 30,878.58 and traded 2.1 percent down at 30,217.71 by
10:15 a.m. Anglo American, which comprises 11 percent of the
gauge, dropped 3.2 percent to 331.64 rand while BHP, the world’s
biggest mining company, retreated 2.6 percent to 246.40 rand,
the weakest since Oct. 29.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  